# VETO — ship frontend (Vercel prebuild)

Vercel **does not** run `flutter build`; it only serves committed **`frontend/build/web`**.

## Before pushing web/UI changes to `main`

From **repo root**:

```bash
npm run ship:web
```

This runs `flutter build web` (with production `VETO_API_BASE`) and `vercel:check`. Then **stage and commit** everything under `frontend/build/web` that changed, plus any edits in `frontend/web/` (e.g. `index.html`, `gemini_live.mjs`).

## Do not

- Push only `frontend/web/*` without rebuilding and committing `frontend/build/web` when Dart or web assets changed.
- Leave fixes only on feature branches if production should update — **merge to `main`** so GitHub → Vercel/Render auto-deploy hooks run.

## Backend (Render)

`render.yaml` sets **`branch: main`** and **`autoDeployTrigger: commit`** — every push to `main` deploys **`veto_legal`** (not only when `backend/` changes). If the dashboard had auto-deploy off, sync the Blueprint once so YAML applies.

## Frontend (Vercel via GitHub Actions)

On **`push` to `main`**, `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` builds Flutter and deploys to Vercel prod. Analyze/test run with **`continue-on-error`** so a failing test does not skip the deploy (warnings appear in the workflow log).
